# system-janitor configuration
#
# Sourced as bash. Use shell expansions and comments freely.
# Copy to ~/.config/system-janitor/config and edit.

# ── Workspace dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories scanned for .NET build artifacts
# (bin/ and obj/). The script walks up to 6 levels deep.
#
# JANITOR_WORKSPACE_DIRS="$HOME/code:$HOME/projects"

# ── Extra cleanup dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories to remove entirely on every run.
# Useful for caches that aren't covered by the built-in sections.
#
# Examples (uncomment selectively):
#
#   JANITOR_EXTRA_CLEANUP_DIRS="$HOME/.cache/some-tool:$HOME/.cache/playwright-old"

# ── Safety-floor dirs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories whose inode AND total byte size
# must NOT change during the run. If any does, the run exits with code 2
# and logs user.err to syslog.
#
# Use this for paths the cleanup must NEVER touch (active session
# directories, important caches you don't trust to be left alone, etc.).
#
# JANITOR_SAFETY_FLOOR_DIRS="$HOME/.config/important-tool"

# ── Section toggles (defaults: yes if tooling is present) ─────────────
# JANITOR_DOCKER_PRUNE=yes
# JANITOR_DOCKER_VOLUMES=yes        # pass --volumes to docker system prune
# JANITOR_GO_CLEAN=yes
# JANITOR_TMP_GOBUILD_ORPHANS=yes
# JANITOR_NUGET_CLEAN=yes

# ── Log location ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default: $XDG_STATE_HOME/janitor (~/.local/state/janitor)
#
# JANITOR_LOG_DIR="$HOME/.local/state/janitor"
